Unit Callsign: Scar
Unit Type: Light mech

Order Type: Joint Skirmish with the other Light Mechs, Move towards 35N 5W, firing at the powerplant's hostiles, then head north to 38.5N 6W while staying out of range of the Citadel

Facing: The Citadel at all times

Start Cords: 36N - 6W
End Cords: 38.5N - 6W 

RP:
*Week 2*

**High Command** changed my callsign to **Scar.** I have to say, I like the sound of it.
While escorting the **Beach Bunny**, we received a request for backup from operation **Blackout**, and decided to assist them.
We arrived just on time to prevent any friendly losses, but in doing so, got split up from our main forces.
After the fight, we received intel on **The Citadel**. It seems their defenses cover half of the **Power Plant**. Good thing we didn't approach it from the north. Godspeed **Griffer**.
**Tardigrade**'s pilot suggested we clean up the remaining units at the Plant and regroup north with our main forces. A couple of us wanted to help CO **Tabby**, but the final vote was in favor of the initial proposal. Luckily, our initial flanking cleaned most of them out, so we should be able to regroup with our retreating Light Vehicles at the very least.
...
As I finish this journal entry, I realize I've fallen for the off by 1 error yet again when naming said entries. Oh well, it's not like I can edit the previous one. 
Scar out.

RP:
Week 2
For us it was quiet when we disembarked, but I could hear combat all around the area.
Then we started to take a few shots from a nearby powerplant.
Not a lot, they were focused on our other teams. We fire back to cover them, but our mission is the same:
scout the north, keep out of range of the citadel, bring peace and order to this place.
